sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J70090
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This is used to test whether the protein fusion Bioscaffold part (BBa_J70032, PpiI and PsrI) can be used to make protein fusions (can also be cut with BamHI) from BioBricks with normal heads and tails.
Note that J70032 is a composite part made up of J70030, J70031, and J70012.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Julie Norville
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Location of protein heads and tails and location of PpiI and PsrI cut sites.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J70042
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: 6his part for use with BioScaffold parts ATG-6his-GGATCC (glycine serine)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This 7 His prefix tag and be used with BBa_J70010 (PpiI) and BBa_J70012 (PsrI) in fusing a 6 his tag to the N-terminus of a protein. This part is still in testing. During the BioScaffold part excision, it should be placed in pSB2K3.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Julie Norville
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This can be used when creating standard fusions between the 6 his tag and protein parts using BioScaffold parts.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J70030
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: A BioScaffold Part (Uses PpiI), Protein Tail Remover see Part Design Page
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: When placed in a BioBrick assembly and cut with the restriction enzyme PpiI, this part will direct the restriction enzymes to cut outside the BioBrick scar still in testing, uses restriction enzyme sites PpiI (2) PacI (2) MabI (2), will place in pSB1AK3 vector
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Julie Norville
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Can be used to removed protein tails for protein fusions, see BBF RFC 15

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J70031
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Linker for BioScaffold Parts, example of Gamma BioScaffold part
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Will use as a linker when fusing two BioScaffold parts, can be created as an oligo
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Julie Norville
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: needs to be longer than 28 bp

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J70012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: A BioScaffold Part (Uses PsrI), Protein Head Remover see Part Design page
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Julie Norville

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J70048
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: 6his part for use with BioScaffold parts ATG-GGATCC (glycine serine)-6 His-TAA
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This 6 His suffix tag can be used with BBa_J70012 (PsrI) in fusing a 6 his tag to the C-terminus of a protein. This part is still in testing. During the BioScaffold part excision, it should be placed in pSB2K4.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Julie Norville
